feat(seo): deepen category/country pages, add ItemList/FAQ schema + OG images

Acts on the SEO/GEO baseline audit findings (thin programmatic content was the
top issue):
- Category & country data pages: second summary paragraph, two question-based
  H2 sections (funding difficulty vs site-wide average, realistic goal from
  median/avg of successful campaigns), and a data-driven FAQ section. Roughly
  doubles on-page word count with fact-first, AI-citable copy.
- seo.ts: add itemListLd() (top-campaign lists) and faqLd() (FAQPage);
  formatUsdCompact now supports billions ($1.4B).
- db.ts: add getCategoryFundingStats/getCountryFundingStats (USD median/avg of
  successful campaigns) and getOverallSuccessRate for comparisons.
- Add dedicated opengraph-image routes for category & country pages (were
  missing OG images).
- Homepage H1 -> "Kickstarter Analytics, Decoded" (keyword-richer).
- llms.txt advertises the new ItemList/FAQPage + Q&A insights.
- ORG_SAME_AS left as a documented placeholder pending real owned profiles.
